title: American Horror Stories Episode 7 Game Over Review
author: MaryGirl Moody
comment: I actually hated this one lmao. I despise ruby, the son was annoying, bad acting. Get it together ryan.
When I heard Ben Harmon crying I thought “oh no it’s THE TEARJERKER” & covered my eyes… LOL
In my opinion, Ba'al,Feral and Drive In are the only episodes worthy of the AHS name in this cringefest for a spinoff. The rest didn't happen.
I adore how meta it was, basically Ryan & Brad making fun of themselves. Agreed Addie was a total waste. I wish Murder House would have imploded though. Done with it.

First, I totally want to see a Telltale game about AHS now thanks to this episode, with the idea of every chapter based on each season of it, or an RPG game based on it. I would love that. 😅

And second, I think that episode felt rushed and dugging more holes to the plot, it shouldn't have existed and the whole 'burning the MH down' should have kept for the series finale. That's it.
